  "text": "The SotubMCs genes expression under biotic and abiotic stresses and in different hormonal treatments was analyzed using Illumina RNA-Sequencing datasets generated by the PGSC (The Potato Genome Sequencing Consortium, 2011; [CITATION_1] . For biotic stress, detached potato leaves were inoculated with Phytophthora infestans inoculum (Pi isolate US8: Pi02-007), 100 mg/ml acibenzolar-S-methyl (BTH) and 2 mg/ml DL-b-amino-n-butyric acid (BABA). To mimic herbivory response, primary and secondary leaves were wounded. For abiotic stress treatments 35 C heat, 150 mM NaCl and 260 mM mannitol were used. To induce hormonal stress, 50 mM Abscisic acid (ABA), 10 mM indole-3-acetic acid (IAA), 50 mM gibberellic acid (GA3), and 10 mM 6-benzyl amino purine (BAP) was used. The treatments were given for 24 h on in vitro grown plants.",
